# TickTalk Service Portal Demo — project rules

## Source of truth

- **`reference/*.pptx`** (primary deck) defines **business logic**, **flow structure**, **UI/UX direction**, **visual hierarchy**, and **wording intent**.
- **`docs/ai-instructions.md`**, **`docs/user-flows.md`**, **`docs/copy-notes.md`**, **`docs/requirements.md`** refine execution; on conflict with the PPT on **policy/eligibility**, follow the PPT or record ambiguity (below)—not AI inference alone.

## Copy & tone

- **Native US English**; **mobile-readable**: short sentences, scannable bullets, **concise CTAs** (see `docs/copy-notes.md`).
- **Premium, parent-friendly, modern SaaS**: warm, clear, not stiff or “translated.”
- If copy is too long for small screens, **shorten without changing meaning**.

## Do not invent policy

Never change or assume final rules for **warranty**, **return eligibility**, **Care+**, or **RMA** behavior without **`docs/open-questions.md`** (Question / Why it matters / Suggested approaches). Same for any **new** business rule.

## UI priorities

- **Mobile-first**; **touch-friendly** spacing; **simple card-based** layouts; **clean type**; low-stress paths.
- **Reuse** `src/components/` patterns; **Tailwind** utilities + shared spacing; avoid one-off magic numbers unless extending the theme.
- **Avoid**: long paragraphs in UI, heavy jargon, clutter, **unnecessary modals**, **deep nesting** of cards.

## Stack

- **React + TypeScript**; keep components typed and route/screens thin where possible.

## Mocks vs backend

- **Mock data first**; **no undocumented real API contracts**.
- **Unclear product logic** → **`docs/open-questions.md`**, not guesses in code or copy.

## PPT vs mobile UX

- If layout from the deck hurts **mobile usability**, simplify the **presentation** while preserving **business intent**, and log gaps in **`docs/open-questions.md`** when customer-facing promises are affected.
